ars-Erik Englund]]\n| officeholder_sort = Englund, Lars-Erik\n| born_year         = 1934\n| died_year         = 2010\n| term_start        = 1 July 1994\n| term_end          = 30 September 1994\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|1994|7|1|1994|9|30}}\n| ref               =<ref name=\"Flygvapennytt (1994), p. 2\"/>\n\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 12\n| image             = \n| military_rank     = Lieutenant general\n| officeholder      = [[Kent Harrskog]]\n| officeholder_sort = Harrskog, Kent\n| born_year         = 1944\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 1 October 1994\n| term_end          = 30 June 1998\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|1994|10|1|1998|9|30}}\n| ref               =<ref name=\"Flygvapennytt (1994), p. 2\"/><ref name=\"Flygvapennytt (1998), pp. 2-3\">{{cite journal |url=http://www.aef.se/Flygvapnet/Tidskrifter/FV_Nytt/Flygvapennytt_1998-2.pdf |journal=Flygvapennytt |publisher=Flygstaben |title=Flygvapnets fr\u00e4mste f\u00f6retr\u00e4dare: Generalmajor JAN JONSSON |number=2 |year=1998 |location=Stockholm |language=Swedish |id={{LIBRIS|8257600}} |pages=2\u20133}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Officeholder table end}}\n\n===Inspectors General of the Air Force===\n{{Officeholder table start\n| showorder          = y\n| showimage          = y\n| officeholder_title = Inspector General of the Air Force<br>''Generalinspekt\u00f6r f\u00f6r flygvapnet''\n| showparty          = n\n| showtermlenght     = y\n| showref            = y\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 13\n| image             = \n| military_rank     = Major general\n| officeholder      = [[Jan Jonsson (Swedish Air Force officer)|Jan Jonsson]]\n| officeholder_sort = Jonsson, Jan\n| born_year         = 1952\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 1 July 1998\n| term_end          = 30 June 2000\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|1998|7|1|2000|6|30}}\n| ref               =<ref name=\"Flygvapennytt (1998), pp. 2-3\"/><ref name=\"Liander (2000), p. 38\">{{cite journal |url=http://www.fht.nu/bilder/Flygvapnet/Flygvapennytt/fv_nytt_2_2000_ny_gi_for_fv.pdf |journal=Flygvapennytt |publisher=Flygstaben |title=Mats Nilsson. Ny GI f\u00f6r flygvapnet. |first=Peter |last=Liander |number=2 |year=2000 |location=Stockholm |language=Swedish |id={{LIBRIS|8257600}} |page=38}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 14\n| image             = First Marshal of the Court Lieutenant General Mats Nilsson in 2013.jpg\n| military_rank     = Major general\n| officeholder      = [[Mats Nilsson (Swedish Air Force officer)|Mats Nilsson]]\n| officeholder_sort = Nilsson, Mats\n| born_year         = 1956\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 1 July 2000\n| term_end          = 1 December 2002\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|2000|7|1|2002|12|1}}\n| ref               =<ref name=\"Liander (2000), p. 38\"/><ref name=\"Liander (2002), p. 5\">{{cite journal |url=http://www.fht.nu/bilder/Flygvapnet/Flygvapennytt/fv_nytt_4_2002_jan_andersson_ny_gi.pdf |journal=Flygvapennytt |publisher=Flygstaben |title=Mats Nilsson l\u00e4mnar GI-posten. Jan Andersson tar \u00f6ver |first=Peter |last=Liander |number=4 |year=2002 |location=Stockholm |language=Swedish |id={{LIBRIS|8257600}} |page=5}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 15\n| image             = \n| military_rank     = Major general\n| officeholder      = [[Jan Andersson (Swedish Air Force officer)|Jan Andersson]]\n| officeholder_sort = Andersson, Jan\n| born_year         = 1955\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 1 January 2003<ref name=\"Liander (2002), p. 5\"/>\n| term_end          = 2003\n| timeinoffice      = {{age in years|2003|2003}} years\n| ref               = -\n}}\n{{Officeholder table end}}\n\n===Inspectors of the Air Force===\n{{Officeholder table start\n| showorder          = y\n| showimage          = y\n| officeholder_title = Inspector of the Air Force<br>''Flygvapeninspekt\u00f6r''\n| showparty          = n\n| showtermlenght     = y\n| showref            = y\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 15\n| image             = \n| military_rank     = Major general\n| officeholder      = [[Jan Andersson (Swedish Air Force officer)|Jan Andersson]]\n| officeholder_sort = Andersson, Jan\n| born_year         = 1955\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 2003\n| term_end          = 29 February 2008\n| timeinoffice      = {{age in years|2003|2008}} years\n| ref               = -\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 16\n| image             = 2014 Silwer 20.jpg\n| military_rank     = Major general\n| officeholder      = [[Anders Silwer]]\n| officeholder_sort = Silwer, Anders\n| born_year         = 1959\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 1 March 2008\n| term_end          = 31 December 2011\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|2008|3|1|2011|12|31}}\n| ref               =<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.forsvarsmakten.se/sv/information-och-fakta/var-historia/artiklar/vikbo-1960/ |publisher=[[Swedish Armed Forces]] |title=VIKBO 1960 |access-date=27 October 2017 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 17\n| image             = General Micael Byd\u00e9n.jpg\n| military_rank     = Major general\n| officeholder      = [[Micael Byd\u00e9n]]\n| officeholder_sort = Byd\u00e9n, Micael\n| born_year         = 1964\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 1 January 2012\n| term_end          = 2014\n| timeinoffice      = {{age in years|2012|2014}} years\n| ref               =<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogg.forsvarsmakten.se/flygvapenbloggen/2012/01/01/i-ny-befattning/ |publisher=[[Swedish Armed Forces]] |title=I NY BEFATTNING! |first=Micael |last=Byd\u00e9n |date=1 January 2012 |access-date=27 October 2017 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Officeholder table end}}\n\n===Chiefs of Air Force===\n{{Officeholder table start\n| showorder          = y\n| showimage          = y\n| officeholder_title = Chief of Air Force<br>''Flygvapenchef''\n| showparty          = n\n| showtermlenght     = y\n| showref            = y\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 17\n| image             = General Micael Byd\u00e9n.jpg\n| military_rank     = Major general\n| officeholder      = [[Micael Byd\u00e9n]]\n| officeholder_sort = Byd\u00e9n, Micael\n| born_year         = 1964\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 2014\n| term_end          = 30 September 2015\n| timeinoffice      = {{age in years|2014|2015}} years\n| ref               = -\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 18\n| image             = 2018-11-28, Swedish Air Force pilots receive USAF Air Medal, Major General Mats Helgesson (45203706625).jpg\n| military_rank     = Major general\n| officeholder      = [[Mats Helgesson]]\n| officeholder_sort = Helgesson, Mats\n| born_year         = 1964\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 1 October 2015\n| term_end          = 1 October 2019\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|2015|10|1|2019|10|1}}\n| ref               = <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.forsvarsmakten.se/sv/aktuellt/2015/09/mats-helgesson-ny-flygvapenchef/ |publisher=[[Swedish Armed Forces]] |title=Mats Helgesson ny flygvapenchef |trans-title=Mats Helgesson new Chief of Air Force |date=17 September 2015 |access-date=27 October 2017 |language=Swedish}}</ref><ref name=\"FM (2019)\">{{cite web |url=https://www.forsvarsmakten.se/sv/aktuellt/2019/09/ny-flygvapenchef-utsedd/ |publisher=[[Swedish Armed Forces]] |title=Ny flygvapenchef utsedd |trans-title=New Chief of Air Force appointed |date=5 September 2019 |access-date=5 September 2019 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 19\n| image             = \n| military_rank     = Major general\n| officeholder      = [[Carl-Johan Edstr\u00f6m]]\n| officeholder_sort = Edstr\u00f6m, Carl-Johan\n| born_year         = 1967\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 1 October 2019\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|2019|10|1}}\n| ref               = <ref name=\"FM (2019)\"/>\n}}\n{{Officeholder table end}}\n\n==List of deputy chiefs==\n===Deputy Chiefs of Air Force===\n{{Officeholder table start\n| showorder          = n\n| showimage          = y\n| officeholder_title = Deputy Chief of Air Force<br>''St\u00e4llf\u00f6retr\u00e4dande flygvapenchef''\n| showparty          = n\n| showtermlenght     = y\n| showref            = y\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = \n| image             = \n| military_rank     = Brigadier general\n| officeholder      = [[Carl-Johan Edstr\u00f6m]]\n| officeholder_sort = Edstr\u00f6m, Carl-Johan\n| born_year         = 1967\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 1 January 2019\n| term_end          = 30 September 2019\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|2019|1|1|2019|9|30}}\n| ref               = <ref name=\"FM (2019)\"/>\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = \n| image             = \n| military_rank     = Brigadier general\n| officeholder      = [[Anders Persson (Swedish Air Force officer)|Anders Persson]]\n| officeholder_sort = Persson, Anders\n| born_year         = 1968\n| died_year         = \n| term_start        = 1 October 2019\n| timeinoffice      = {{ayd|2019|10|1}}\n| ref               = <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.forsvarsmakten.se/sv/aktuellt/2019/10/ny-flygvapenchef-tog-befalet/ |publisher=[[Swedish Armed Forces]] |title=Ny flygvapenchef tog bef\u00e4let |first=Angela |last=Ullman |date=2 October 2019 |access-date=9 October 2019 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Officeholder table end}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Chief of Army (Sweden)]]\n*[[Chief of Navy (Sweden)]]\n\n==Footnotes==\n<references group=\"note\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{Staffs of the Swedish Armed Forces}}\n{{Chief of the air force by country}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chief of Air Force (Sweden)}}\n[[Category:Air force chiefs of staff|Sweden]]\n[[Category:Swedish Air Force]]\n[[Category:Swedish Air Force generals| ]]\n[[Category:Military appointments of Sweden]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox official post\n| post                     = Chief\n| body                     = Air Force\n| native_name              = ''Flygvapenchef''\n| insignia                 = \n| insigniasize             = \n| insigniacaption          = \n| flag                     = Kommandotecken Flygvapenchefen.svg\n| flagsize                 = \n| flagborder               = \n| flagcaption              = Command flag of the Chief of Air Force.\n| image                    = \n| imagesize                = \n| alt                      = \n| incumbent                = Major general [[Carl-Johan Edstr\u00f6m]]\n| acting                     =\n| incumbentsince           = 1 October 2019\n| department               = [[Swedish Air Force]]\n| style                    = \n| type                     = \n| status                   = \n| abbreviation             = \n| member_of                = \n| reports_to               = The Chief of Swedish Armed Forces Training and Development<ref name=\"PRODUKTIONSLEDNINGEN\">{{cite web |url=http://www.forsvarsmakten.se/sv/organisation/hogkvarteret/produktionsledningen/ |publisher=[[Swedish Armed Forces]] |title=PRODUKTIONSLEDNINGEN |access-date=10 March 2016 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n| residence                = \n| seat                     = Liding\u00f6v\u00e4gen 24, [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]] \n| nominator                = [[Minister for Defence (Sweden)|Minister for Defence]]\n| appointer                = The [[Government of Sweden|Government]]\n| appointer_qualified      = \n| termlength               = \n| termlength_qualified     = \n| constituting_instrument  = \n| precursor                = \n| formation                = 1 July 1926\n| first                    = [[Karl Amundson]]\n| last                     = \n| abolished                = \n| succession               = \n| unofficial_names         = \n| deputy                   = \n| salary                   = \n| website                  = \n}}\n\n'''Chief of Air Force''' ({{lang-sv|Flygvapenchef}}, FVC) is the most senior appointment in the [[Swedish Air Force]]. The position Chief of Air Force was introduced in 1926 and the current form in 2014.\n\n==History==\nThe position and the staff agency \"Chief of the Air Force\" ({{lang-sv|Chefen f\u00f6r flygvapnet}}, CFA) was created for a central leadership of the Air Force in peacetime<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ne.se/uppslagsverk/encyklopedi/l%C3%A5ng/chefen-f%C3%B6r-flygvapnet |work=[[Nationalencyklopedin]] |title=Chefen f\u00f6r flygvapnet |access-date=11 March 2016 |language=Swedish}}</ref><ref name=\"F\u00f6rsvarets traditioner\">{{cite book |title=F\u00f6rsvarets traditioner i framtiden med \u00f6versiktlig historik fr\u00e5n 1500-talet |url=http://www.sfhm.se/globalassets/global/sfhm_ny/traditionsnamden/2015/traditionsskriften-14-12-22--underlag-for-pdf.pdf |year=2015 |publisher=Statens f\u00f6rsvarshistoriska museer TradN |language=Swedish |isbn=9789197859554 |id={{LIBRIS|17552963}} |page=12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161024233957/http://www.sfhm.se/globalassets/global/sfhm_ny/traditionsnamden/2015/traditionsskriften-14-12-22--underlag-for-pdf.pdf |archivedate=2016-10-24 }}</ref> through the formation of the Swedish Air Force as an independent military branch which took place on 1 July 1926.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.f18.se/joomla/images/stories/tidningen/F18tidn_nr42.pdf |journal=F18-kamraten: tidning f\u00f6r F18 kamratf\u00f6rening med medlemmar ur Kungl S\u00f6dert\u00f6rns flygflottilj/flygvapnets S\u00f6dert\u00f6rnsskolor |title=Lars-Erik Englund, flygvapenchef 1988\u20131994 |year=2010 |publisher=F18 kamratf\u00f6rening |location=Uttran |language=Swedish |id={{LIBRIS|10339544}} |number=42 |page=3}}</ref> Following a larger reorganization of the [[Swedish Armed Forces]] in 1994, the staff agency Chief of the Air Force ceased to exist as an independent agency. Instead, the post Chief of Air Force Staff ({{lang-sv|Chefen f\u00f6r flygvapenledningen}}) was created at the then newly instituted [[Swedish Armed Forces Headquarters]]. In 1998, the Swedish Armed Forces was again reorganized. Most of the duties of the Chief of Air Force Staff were transferred to the newly instituted post of \"[[Inspector General]] of the Air Force\" ({{lang-sv|Generalinspekt\u00f6ren f\u00f6r flygvapnet}}). The post is similar to that of the \"Inspector General of the [[Swedish Army|Army]]\" ({{lang-sv|Generalinspekt\u00f6ren f\u00f6r arm\u00e9n}}) and the \"Inspector General of the [[Navy]]\" ({{lang-sv|Generalinspekt\u00f6ren f\u00f6r marinen}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://data.riksdagen.se/dokument/GL02F%C3%B63 |publisher=[[Riksdag]] |title=Motion till riksdagen 1997/98:F\u00f63 |author=Nordgren, Annika |date=24 February 1998 |access-date=11 March 2016 |language=Swedish|display-authors=etal}}</ref> It was later renamed to \"Inspector of the Air Force\" ({{lang-sv|Flygvapeninspekt\u00f6ren}}).<ref name=\"F\u00f6rsvarets traditioner\"/>\n\nOn 1 January 2014, the \"Chief of Air Force\" ({{lang-sv|Flygvapenchefen}}, FVC) position was reinstated in the Swedish Armed Forces. The position has not the same duties as before.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.forsvarsmakten.se/sv/aktuellt/2013/12/nya-namn-pa-nya-poster/?section=15809 |publisher=[[Swedish Armed Forces]] |title=Nya namn p\u00e5 nya poster |trans-title=New names for new positions |date=20 December 2013 |access-date=11 March 2016 |language=Swedish}}</ref>\n\n==Tasks==\nTasks of the Chief of Air Force:<ref>{{cite book |title=F\u00f6rsvarets f\u00f6rfattningssamling: FFS 2013:4 |date=2013-12-23 |publisher=TF-redaktionen, F\u00f6rsvarets materielverk |location=Stockholm |language=sv |issn=0347-7576 |id={{LIBRIS|3683131}} |page=18 |url=http://www.forsvarsmakten.se/siteassets/4-om-myndigheten/dokumentfiler/lagrum/upphavda-foreskrifter/ffs-2013-4-fmarbo.pdf}}</ref>\n*Lead the units which the Chief of Swedish Armed Forces Training and Development has distributed\n*To the Chief of Swedish Armed Forces Training and Development propose the development of the units' abilities\n*Being the foremost representative of the units\n*Represent the units and the area of ability in international contacts\n\n==Heraldry==\nThe command flag of the Chief of Air Force is drawn by Brita Grep and embroidered by hand by the company Libraria. [[Blazon]]: \"Fessed in yellow and blue; on yellow two blue batons of command with sets of open yellow crowns placed two and one in saltire, on blue a winged two-bladed yellow propeller.\"<ref>{{cite book |url=http://www.sfhm.se/contentassets/84a6e4f1b2ce4e2b96c4ba578a41c503/sfhm-skriftserie_svenska-armens-falttecken-efter-millennieskiftet_av_christian-braunstein.pdf |last=Braunstein |first=Christian |title=Svenska f\u00f6rsvarsmaktens f\u00e4lttecken efter millennieskiftet |trans-title=The flags and standards of the Swedish armed forces after the turn of the millennium |series=Skrift / Statens f\u00f6rsvarshistoriska museer, 1101-7023 ; 7 [dvs 8] |year=2004 |publisher=Statens f\u00f6rsvarshistoriska museer |location=Stockholm |language=Swedish |isbn=91-971584-7-X |id={{LIBRIS|9815350}} |page=108 |access-date=2018-06-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522042235/http://www.sfhm.se/contentassets/84a6e4f1b2ce4e2b96c4ba578a41c503/sfhm-skriftserie_svenska-armens-falttecken-efter-millennieskiftet_av_christian-braunstein.pdf |archive-date=2018-05-22 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==List of chiefs==\n===Chiefs of Air Force===\n{{Officeholder table start\n| showorder          = y\n| showimage          = y\n| officeholder_title = Chief of the Air Force<br>''Chefen f\u00f6r flygvapnet''\n| showparty          = n\n| showtermlenght     = y\n| showref            = y\n}}\n{{Officeholder table\n| order             = 1\n| image             = Amundson4.jpeg\n| military_rank     = Major general\n| officeholder      = [[Karl Amundson]]\n| officeholder_sort = Amundson, Karl\n| born_year         = 1873\n| died_year         = 1938\n| term_start        = 1 July 1926\n| term_end          = 25 February 1